## Issues with Java 8 Compatibility

### 1. Multiple Inheritance Issue in test2.java
The first major issue is in your [test2.java](test23/test2.java) file. Java doesn't support multiple inheritance from classes. The line:

```java
public class test2 extends A,B{
```

This will cause a compilation error because Java only allows extending one class at a time.

### 2. Switch Expression Compatibility in GradingCategoryTest.java
In your [GradingCategoryTest.java](src/test/java/com/challenge/gradebook/GradingCategoryTest.java), you're using switch expressions which were introduced in Java 14:

```java
String result = switch (category) {
    case HOMEWORK -> "Homework assignments";
    case QUIZZES -> "Quiz assessments";
    case MIDTERM -> "Midterm examination";
    case FINAL_EXAM -> "Final examination";
};
```

## Java 8 Compatible Solutions

Here are the corrected versions:

```java::test2.java::test23/test2.java
class A {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("A");
    }
}

class B {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("B");
    }
}

// CHANGE: Use interfaces for multiple inheritance-like behavior
interface AInterface {
    default void showA() {
        System.out.println("A");
    }
}

interface BInterface {
    default void showB() {
        System.out.println("B");
    }
}

public class test2 extends A implements AInterface, BInterface {

    @Override
    public void show() {
        super.show(); // Calls A's show method
        showB(); // Calls B's behavior through interface
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        test2 t = new test2();
        t.show();
    }
}
```

