## Problem Analysis
The compilation error "incompatible types: com.challenge.banking.BankingException cannot be converted to java.lang.RuntimeException" was occurring because:

- The `BankingException` class was extending `Exception` (checked exception)
- The test code expected it to be compatible with `RuntimeException` (unchecked exception)
- This created a type incompatibility since `Exception` and `RuntimeException` are different branches in the exception hierarchy

## Solution Applied
Changed the inheritance hierarchy of `BankingException` from extending `Exception` to extending `RuntimeException`. This modification:

✅ **Resolves the type incompatibility** - BankingException is now a RuntimeException  
✅ **Maintains all existing functionality** - All constructors and methods remain unchanged  
✅ **Preserves test compatibility** - All existing tests will continue to work  
✅ **Follows common banking exception patterns** - Most custom business exceptions extend RuntimeException  

